Let $A$ be the perigee, let $B$ be the apogee, let $F$ be the focus where the sun is, let $O$ be the center of the ellipse, and let $M$ be the current position of Xavier.

[asy]
unitsize(1 cm);

pair A, B, F, M, O;

path ell = xscale(2)*Circle((0,0),1);

A = (-2,0);
B = (2,0);
F = (-sqrt(3),0);
O = (0,0);
M = (0,-1);

draw(ell);
draw(A--M);
draw(O--M);
draw(F--M);
