dot("$A$", A, W);
dot("$B$", B, E);
dot("$F$", F, N);
dot("$M$", M, S);
dot("$O$", O, N);
[/asy]

Then $AB$ is a major axis of the ellipse, and $AB = 2 + 12 = 14.$  Since $M$ is the midway point, $MF = AO = \frac{14}{2} = \boxed{7}.$

